BOY OH BOYD! 

George Boyd typifies what has been good about Burnley this season. He works so hard for his manager and his team-mates, but he’s also got that little bit of quality to go with it.

He scored a fantastic goal against Man City — it was superb technique and such a pure strike — but I was so impressed by his work ethic. 

He covered 8.4 miles on Saturday — the fourth-highest distance in the league this season. And, incredibly, of the top 10 distances run in 2014-15, six of them belong to Boyd. That is an incredible effort and exactly what managers want.

