BLUES ARE BACK 

It's been a good week for Everton in a very tough season. The first half-hour against Dynamo Kiev was painful to watch last week — there was almost an anger around the ground at the way the team were playing. 

They had to fight so hard to get that win but you saw what it did for their confidence — they followed it with a big result against Newcastle.

I never felt they were in danger of being relegated and now they could go on a run and might even be England’s last team standing in Europe. 

